Here's the full, current set of install commands — everything you actually need, nothing extra:

**1. System packages**
```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y python3-dev
```

**2. Python venv + packages**
```bash
cd ~/projects/AteentionDriftAgent
python3 -m venv venv          # skip if venv already exists
source venv/bin/activate
pip install requests evdev
```

**3. Input device permissions (one-time, only if not already done)**
```bash
sudo usermod -aG input $USER
```
Then log out and log back in (or `newgrp input` for just the current shell).

**4. GNOME Window Calls extension (one-time, only if not already done)**
```bash
cd /tmp
git clone https://github.com/ickyicky/window-calls.git
mkdir -p ~/.local/share/gnome-shell/extensions/window-calls@domandoman.xyz
cp /tmp/window-calls/extension.js /tmp/window-calls/metadata.json ~/.local/share/gnome-shell/extensions/window-calls@domandoman.xyz/
```
Log out/in, then:
```bash
gnome-extensions enable window-calls@domandoman.xyz
```

**5. Run the agent**
```bash
cd ~/projects/AteentionDriftAgent
source venv/bin/activate
python3 -m agent.runner
```


